quran[3]{c,v,t}:
  22,23,"God will admit those who believe and work righteous deeds, to gardens with rivers flowing through them. They will be adorned therein with bracelets of gold and pearls, and their garments will be of silk"
  22,24,"For they have been guided to the most refined of speeches, they have been guided to the path of Him Who is worthy of praise"
  22,25,"As for those who have rejected God, and would keep back the people from the way of God, and from the Sacred Masjid which We have made for all people, must know that equal there is the resident and the visitor, and any whose purpose for being there is deviation or wrongdoing, We will cause them to taste a most terrible penalty"